<br>
GMs on the other hand are like rolling a dice.  I have gotten a few cool ones when my UI was going crazy but some real asses for things that were serious to me.  They may hear it ten times a day but that is their job.  Maybe they should fix the problem players and they won't hear it as much.<br>
<br>
I signed up for the guide program once awhile ago.  Halfway in I knew it wasn't for me but thought I would try it.  I got up to where they assign you a server and log in your character to be made a guide and the GM asked me if I was told about requesting vacation time.  That was the final thing for me and I stepped out before I was guided.<br>
<br>
The manual they give you is interesting.  I really don't see why they don't make it public.  There are dozens of things guides can't do that would surprise people and probably pisses them off in game when a guide can't do it but they don't understand why.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is be nice to them.  They aren't all tech people and have their hands tied on many things. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/utalzarbbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talzar BBH</A> at: 9/17/02 11:10:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugattaka451.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gattaka451</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~gattaka/_uimages/danceman.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Makes babies cry</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/18/02 12:28:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~gattaka/_uimages/danceman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Solid Read</span><hr size=1> I'll be eager to see what happens with the CS. I feel that if they do make it where you have to pay, there will be a mass exodus of people. But on the other hand, until anything else that comes out, people will probably still play EQ. I heard the other day that Shadowbane got pushed back again. Ugh. <p><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~gattaka/_uimages/calvinfaces.gif"></img>
