<br>
The candid response &quot;I have never heard of that bug before, sorry there is nothing I can do you had better use the /report system&quot;<br>
<br>
I used the report system and came across the same bug again, I get the same candid response followed by my reply that I have already /reported it.  <br>
<br>
My response (again candid) is:  &quot;sorry we dont have any logs of this /report&quot;.  <br>
<br>
Scenario 1<br>
----------<br>
PoG (Around January 2001) - I had a corpse in there when it was a tough zone to hit.  I plan, plan, plan to ensure that I am 100% covered without pulling on too many other people.  I decide to move Roluvin (monk) to PoG because he is not kos.  I get him there move the corpse successfully.  I got an invis move Raluvin into PoG - find and begin looting my corpse.  Due to lag I get about 60% of the corpse looted before I have the Protectors on me - I quickly grab my CT gate potion and use it - leaving around 3 backpacks on me.  <br>
<br>
Servers go down....I logged Raluvin back in - camped CT gate potions for a bit - get 2 and headed over to PoG again.  I got another invis zoned in and went for my corpse which I couldnt find.  Invis wore off - I gated. <br>
<br>
Logged Roluvin in and scoured PoG no sign of corpse so I petitioned.  <br>
<br>
I was told it would need to be referred to the lead GM and I would have to petition everyday.  <br>
<br>
ONE WEEK it took before I FINALLY got a hold of the lead GM and I was basically told there was nothing I could do.  <br>
<br>
I didnt fight it, because I couldnt be arsed - but at that time the 3 backpacks I lost equated to around 50-60k worth of stuff at that time. <br>
<br>
Scenario 2<br>
----------<br>
We were buffing up for a big mob kill and was preparing to kill it - another guild turned up and called in a gm (how sad people cannot resolve things amiciably).  We had around another 5-6 people inc at the time.  <br>
<br>
The other raid moved directly behind us (thus increasing lag) and were speaking to the GM.  The GM informed us we had exactly 5 mins to engage the mob before the other raid took over.  No mention of them moving away from us or anything to decrease lag.  Our clerics could not heal or anything.  Result:  other raid let us take the mob to around 30% engaged and finished it off.   <br>
<br>
There was opinion that the guide in question was friends of the so-called GM.  <br>
<br>
Scenario 3<br>
----------<br>
There was an old rogue friend I used to have.  I was selling a Granite Face Grinder which at the time was worth in excess of 50k.  I was offered 2 items for it - a Heiro Cloak and something else which I do not recall.   The items were traded and the deal was done.  <br>
<br>
I was in PoH a couple of days when the rogue sent me another tell saying Have you still got the Heiro Cloak which I replied yes.  He said I need it back for a bit, would you mind switching...I was getting suspicious at this time, so I asked why.   I made him go through a whole song and dance act and whilst I was still suspicious, I knew the rogue and he gave me a HBC whilst he took the heiro cloak.  <br>
<br>
Fair enough....just to keep people happy. <br>
<br>
Then I was on Roluvin the following day and the lead GM sent me a tell asking if I was Raluvin to which I replied I was.  He asked me to log onto him which I did.  <br>
<br>
He then asked me if I still had the XXX items to which I replied yes, but the heiro cloak (come to think of it I dont think it was a heiro cloak now, but I will still call it that for the time being).   He asked me how I had acquired these items, so I explained to him how.  <br>
<br>
He said thanks for your help and asked me to remain contactable over the next few days.  <br>
<br>
I then spoke to the rogue in question and said WTF is going on??? and he was all nervous and stuff and asked if he could have the items back.  To which I replied:  No, not until the lead GM and sorted all of this stuff out - and he began offering me all sorts of stuff for the items I had.  I remained vigilant and said I cant do that.  <br>
<br>
The lead GM quit and I had these items on me for over 3 months awaiting a reply - eventually I just gave them away to people I know I could get them back if need be.  <br>
<br>
Overall poor management of the GM guide system imho - and I never saw the rogue again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ugrabem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grabem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Guk Knight</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(9/19/02 7:57:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=526.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Solid Read</span><hr size=1> Well this thread has certainly garnered attention.  It is now on Caster's Realms website.  It has already been responded to by a Sony CS rep.<br>
