<br>
I was level 35ish, fighting in OT with some guildmates.  I had aggro on a mob, the cleric rooted it and I try and back out.  Oh wait go go server lag every time I try and back out I end up right next to the mob a second later.  Cleric is trying to heal me from 5 feet away but getting the message that his target is out of range.  Needless to say I die and come back to loot my body.  Somehow my body has disappeared and is now more than 200 feet away in the direction I was trying to back up in, stuck in the zone wall.  2 hours and 55 minutes go by without a response from a guide or GM (9pm est, prime time imo) so I take cleric rez.  Never did get petition responded to so I take uber 50% rez... I would have at least liked the guide or GM token response telling me it was my 1gig athlon computer with an ethernet connection that was the problem and not their servers... kunark was soooo taxing on the cpu.<br>
<br>
Roomate had a 51 ranger that went on a DN raid.  He camps out to check something online, camps back in and is in a white room with no doors and a bunch of numbers on the wall (GM later told him that was the 'safe box').  After petitioning and waiting for 2 hours my roomate finally escapes the safe box, too bad it took Zland killing him to do it (nice 'safe' box).  GM takes a week to finally respond to his petitions to get his body.<br>
<br>
I've had 5 dire charm pets 'forget' they were dire charmed after their initial mez wore off.  Mez has a mem blur component so I did some testing by mem blurring my pets and that never ever made them break charm.  Of course when I petition about it they can't reset my ability and they haven't ever heard of that bug before.  Funny thing is by the time my petition is normally responded to my 72 minute refresh ability has already popped two or three times. They ask me to do a /bug about it (obviously the first 4 /bug reports didn't help them out much).<br>
<br>
I've accidentally destroyed items due to lag on two occasions.  One time the GM told me I was stuck, the other time the GM replaced the item for me.  Now don't get me wrong, I don't want to look a gifthorse in the mouth but let's try consistency.  <br>
<br>
I've had conversations with some of the morons we flame on these boards.  I had one admit to me in tells that he got flamed pretty badly for something his friend did while playing his account.  I /report this and petition and suprise surprise this moron's account didn't get banned.  It's not like account sharing is against the EULA or anything.<br>
<br>
Let's not even talk about how easy it is to purposefully train someone and get away with it.  The GM's won't accept screenshots as proof, they won't accept log files as proof, they won't take your word as proof, yet they won't take any action without proof.  How incredibly sly of them to set up the rules in such a way that makes them do as little work as possible.<br>
